The use of semidefinite programming relaxations is a common technique in optimization, which suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the traveling salesman problem is a classic problem in this field. The paper could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) since it discusses the integrality gap of different SDP relaxations. Additionally, the paper could belong to cs.OC (Optimization and Control) since it deals with optimization techniques.
